AMD, Lattice, Polycom, SanDisk, Synaptics: U.S. Equity Preview

-- B y   I n y o u n g   H w a n g
-- 
2011-04-21T21:17:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/amd-lattice-polycom-sandisk-synaptics-u-s-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in U.S. trading on April 25. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and prices are as of 4:40 p.m. in
New York.  Advanced Micro Devices Inc. (AMD)  : The second-largest
maker of processors for personal computers reported first-
quarter profit that beat analysts’ predictions, citing demand
for its new chips.  International Game Technology (IGT)   rose 10 percent to
$18. The world’s biggest maker of slot machines reported a
second-quarter adjusted profit of 23 cents a share, topping the
average analyst estimate by 2 cents.  Lattice Semiconductor Corp. (LSCC)   rallied 6.8 percent
to $6.75. The maker of programmable chips reported first-quarter
revenue was $82.6 million, exceeding the average analyst
estimate of $76.5 million.  Maxim Integrated Products Inc. (MXIM)  : The maker of
computer chips reported third-quarter adjusted earnings of 40
cents a share, missing the average analyst estimate by 2 cents.  Polycom Inc. (PLCM)   climbed 6.9 percent to $55.50. The
largest independent maker of videoconference systems said profit
in the first quarter was 48 cents a share excluding some items,
beating the 42-cent average estimate by analysts.  SanDisk Corp. (SNDK)   fell 2.1 percent to $47.95. The
maker of flash-memory cards said adjusted earnings in the first
quarter were $1.03 a share, topping the 99-cent estimate by
analysts on average.  Synaptics Inc. (SYNA)   dropped 1 percent to $27.66. The
maker of touch pads for digital music players and electronic
devices forecast fourth-quarter sales to be no more than $146
million, below the average analyst estimate of $146.7 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Inyoung Hwang at   ihwang7@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 